CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 5, 1956, pg. 31 reads: "Villagers Open - Shown prior to the season's opener in Greater Pittsburgh Baseball League are, left to right, Ray Daniels, infielder; Norman Gant, outfielder, and Pete Peatross, manager, all members of the Terrace Village nine. The opener was called off in the fourth inning because of darkness. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Terrace Village "Villagers" sandlot baseball team players Ray Daniels and Norman Gant, and manager Pete Peatross, standing on Kennard Field
